'''Oyama Shrine''' (おおやまじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Tomika|Q1203855|WD=Q1203855|1=Tomika, Gifu}}, {{ill|lt=Kamo District|Q1348656|WD=Q1348656|1=Kamo District, Gifu}}, {{ill|lt=Gifu Prefecture|Q131277|WD=Q131277|1=Gifu Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}, and its {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=former shrine rank|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|WD=Q712534}} was {{ill|lt=Gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
; Principal deity 
*{{ill|lt=Ōyamazumi|Q386563|WD=Q386563|lt=Ōyamazumi-no-Kami|1=Ōyamatsumi}}

; Merged deities 
*{{ill|WD=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata|Q402376|WD=Q402376|WD=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata-no-Kami|1=Takeminakata}}
*{{ill|WD=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama|Q3080728|WD=Q3080728|WD=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama-no-Kami|1=Ukanomitama}}
*{{ill|WD=Q10921330|lt=Wakumusubi|UNKNOWN|lt=Homusubi-no-Kami|1=Wakumusubi}}
*{{ill|lt=Emperor Ōjin|Q317997|WD=Q317997|1=Emperor Ōjin}} 
*{{ill|lt=Sugawara no Michizane|Q382005|WD=Q382005|1=Sugawara no Michizane}}
*{{ill|lt=Kikurihime|Q11619891|WD=Q11619891|lt=Kikurihime-no-Kami|1=Kikurihime}}

=== History ===
There is a theory identifying it as Oyama Shrine in Kamo District, {{ill|lt=Mino Province|Q864156|WD=Q864156|1=Mino Province}}, listed in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|lt=Shikinaisha register|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}. In the {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|WD=Q184963|1=Edo period}} it was reportedly called "Kamo Myōjin" and "Hakusan-gū."

=== Local information ===
;Location
*{{ill|lt=Gifu Prefecture|Q131277|WD=Q131277|1=Gifu Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Kamo District|Q1348656|WD=Q1348656|1=Kamo District, Gifu}}{{ill|lt=Tomika|Q1203855|WD=Q1203855|1=Tomika, Gifu}} Ōyama 218

;Access
* Nearest bus stop: {{ill|lt=Gifu Bus|Q5560101|WD=Q5560101|1=Gifu Bus}} Seki-Kaminoho Line, get off at "Ōhiraga," then 15 minutes on foot
**From the bus stop it is on the opposite bank of the {{ill|lt=Tsubo River|Q7849905|WD=Q7849905|1=Tsubo River}}.

